main event: A round, oval-shaped, white object was observed in the sky over Baudette, Minnesota for about 30 seconds.
interesting points: The object had an exhaust trail coming from it.
The object just disappeared from view.
The object was smaller in diameter than the beam of a searchlight.
A T-33 aircraft from Duluth AFB was in the area at the time of the sighting, heading 169 degrees.
There were changes in the elevation of the object relative to the horizon during the observation.
